            "Type": 0,
            "Data": "A New Destination",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The race for space between the U.S.S.R. and the U.S. is still going strong, and the U.S.S.R. has achieved more firsts than the U.S.  We are in catchup mode. Both Vostok and the new U.S.S.R. spacecraft \"Voskhod\" is making firsts at a rapid pace such as longest time in orbit, EVA and multi-crew operations in space.",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "During Project Mercury, the president announced the goal of landing astronauts on the Moon. To reach this goal the development of a new program named \"Project Apollo\" was started.\r\n\r\nProject Mercury successfully met its goals of sending astronauts into Earth orbit, and returning them safely back to Earth. Building on its success, a new spacecraft has been developed to further learn and understand how orbital flight works. The program is named \"Project Gemini\".\r\n\r\nBefore sending anyone to the Moon, we need to learn everything needed to do so, and test it. Gemini's objective is to understand and test the space travel techniques needed to support the Apollo mission to land astronauts on the Moon.\r\n\r\nA Lunar Mission needs us to survive in space for up to 14 days, understand the methods of performing extra-vehicular activity (EVA), and the orbital maneuvers necessary to achieve rendezvous and docking with another spacecraft.",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 0,
            "Data": "The Spacecraft",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The Gemini spacecraft is a larger spacecraft with room for two astronauts and has the capability to alter its trajectory in space. The larger spacecraft is divided into three major sections: The Reentry module, the Retro module, and the Equipment module. Both the retro module and the equipment module are separated from the spacecraft before reentry.",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 2,
            "Data": "Gemini_spacecraft.png",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 0,
            "Data": "The Reentry module",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The reentry module is the pressurized crew cabin that makes it possible to survive in space. It is the only part of the spacecraft that makes the entire journey from launch to splashdown. \r\n\r\nIt is powered by two different power sources: batteries as in Project Mercury, and the newly developed Fuel Cells that produce power from cryogenic substances.\r\n\r\nTwo attitude control systems named the RCS is used for attitude control during reentry.\r\n\r\nA state of the art on-board computer (OBC) will aid the crew in performing orbital maneuvers and guidance. Two different types of joysticks provide control of the spacecraft in both yaw, pitch roll, and translational axes (forward, backward, up, down, and sideways). Translation control enables rendezvous, docking, and crew control of the flight path.",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 0,
            "Data": "The Adapter Module",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The Adapter Module consists of both the Retro and the Equipment module. \r\n\r\nThe equipment module consists of most equipment needed during orbital flight. 16 thrusters used for both attitude and translational control is located here, as well as the Fuel Cells and cryogenic substances.\r\n\r\nFour solid-fuel retrorockets are located in the Reentry module, and are fired one-by-one as in Project Mercury.\r\n\r\nThe Equipment module powers the spacecraft in orbit, and is separated before the retrograde burn. After retrograde, the retro section is jettisoned before entry.",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 0,
            "Data": "The Academy",
            "Value": 0
        },
        {
            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The press around the world printed your name in every paper after your heroic efforts in Project Mercury. Your skills and knowledge of the spacecraft was the essentials of your success, and the difference between a safe entry and a disaster. Your veteran skills are needed in Project Gemini, and you will be a commander with your own crew. Martin, the Director of Flight Crew Operation has assigned a newly hired astronaut named Aaron Skye as your co-pilot.\r\n\r\nBefore jumping into your first Gemini flight, it's time to visit the Academy again to get the Gemini License. The Gemini Academy can be found in the \"ACADEMY\" section of the Main Menu and will take you through everything you need to know about this brand-new spacecraft. It's recommended to take a copy of the Reentry Gemini Flight Manual with you to the Academy so you can learn the theory and get a deeper understanding of the spacecraft. The tasks ahead will be complicated, and you will be one of the first to solve them.\r\n\r\nOptional: Once you have completed and received the Gemini Pilot Certificate, let your fellow astronauts know in the Official Reentry Discrod group, where many of the other Gemini astronauts hang out. You can find them in discord.gg/reentrygame.",
            "Value": 0
        },
